											<h4>State Flag</h4>
											<p>The flag is rectangular in the proportion 1:2. The canton which extends at the head halfway to the fly and 2/3 of the hoist to the foot is in icicle blue as the background to a silhouette of Mount Kinabalu, in royal blue, positioned at 1/6 of the height of the canton. The fly is divided equally into three bands of colors, the foot of which extends to the hoist. The top band is zircon blue, followed by white and chili red.</p>
											<p>The new flag and emblem of Sabah are officially established on 16 September 1988. The new State emblems are very similar to the State flag and crest adopted when Sabah joined Malaysia in 1963 but which were replaced in 1981 under administration of Berjaya Party (1976-1985).</p>
